{
  "page": "Seastone Chair",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg/350px-Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"410\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg/525px-Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3c/Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg/700px-Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Xtheseastonechairloganfeliciano.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Seastone Chair by Logan Feliciano © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Seastone Chair</b> is a famous<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> throne of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>, now used as the high seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">House Greyjoy</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lords_of_the_Iron_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lords of the Iron Islands\">Lords of the Iron Islands</a> since <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">Iron Fleet</a> is sworn to the holder of the Seastone Chair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_the_Seastone_Chair\" title=\"Category:Images of the Seastone Chair\">Images of the Seastone Chair</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>The Seastone Chair is made of an immense block of oily <a href=\"/index.php/Black_stone\" title=\"Black stone\">black stone</a> carved into the shape of a great <a href=\"/index.php/Kraken\" title=\"Kraken\">kraken</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Legend says the Seastone Chair was found on the shores of <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Wyk\" title=\"Old Wyk\">Old Wyk</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a> when they came to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Haereg\" title=\"Haereg\">Haereg</a> pondered that the chair was created by a people who inhabited the isles before the First Men, though he eventually dismissed the idea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Kirth\" title=\"Kirth\">Kirth</a> speculated in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Songs_the_Drowned_Men_Sing\" title=\"Songs the Drowned Men Sing\">Songs the Drowned Men Sing</a></i> that the chair was left by a people from across the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Sea\" title=\"Sunset Sea\">Sunset Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Noting similarities between the Seastone Chair and the fused <a href=\"/index.php/Black_stone\" title=\"Black stone\">black stone</a> at the base of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hightower\" title=\"Hightower\">Hightower</a>, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Theron\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Theron\">Theron</a> suggested in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Strange_Stone\" title=\"Strange Stone\">Strange Stone</a></i> that they were the work of so-called <a href=\"/index.php/Deep_Ones\" title=\"Deep Ones\">Deep Ones</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_oldtown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_oldtown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">House Greyjoy</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Pyke\" title=\"Pyke\">Pyke</a> has ruled the Iron Islands since <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_old_way_and_the_new.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_old_way_and_the_new.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> It is unknown if extinct <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_king\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iron king\">iron king</a> dynasties, such as the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\">Greyirons</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">Hoares</a>, used the Seastone Chair as their throne.\n</p><p>After Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Dalton_Greyjoy\" title=\"Dalton Greyjoy\">Dalton Greyjoy</a> was killed by <a href=\"/index.php/Tess\" title=\"Tess\">Tess</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Faircastle\" title=\"Faircastle\">Faircastle</a> without an heir, the Seastone Chair passed by law to his oldest <a href=\"/index.php/Salt_son\" title=\"Salt son\">salt son</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Toron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Toron Greyjoy\">Toron Greyjoy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Seastone Chair is now located on a dais in the Great Hall of the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Keep_of_Pyke\" title=\"Great Keep of Pyke\">Great Keep of Pyke</a>, the seat of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon Greyjoy</a>. His younger brother <a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Damphair</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Priest_of_the_Drowned_God\" title=\"Priest of the Drowned God\">priest of the Drowned God</a>, claims that only a pious ironman can sit the throne, not an ungodly man or a woman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:King_Balon_Throne.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/King_Balon_Throne.jpg/350px-King_Balon_Throne.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/King_Balon_Throne.jpg/525px-King_Balon_Throne.jpg 1.5x, /images/6/69/King_Balon_Throne.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:King_Balon_Throne.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon Greyjoy</a> by Amok ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon Greyjoy</a> declares himself <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_North\" title=\"King of the Isles and the North\">King of the Isles and the North</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The day after Balon falls to his death while crossing <a href=\"/index.php/Pyke\" title=\"Pyke\">Pyke</a>, his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron</a> returns to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> and claims the Seastone Chair. When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Sawane_Botley\" title=\"Sawane Botley\">Sawane Botley</a> objects, Euron Crow's Eye has him drowned.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Opposed to his hated brother Euron succeeding Balon, <a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> insists that a <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot\" title=\"Kingsmoot\">kingsmoot</a> be held to determine the new king,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> but the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot_on_Old_Wyk\" title=\"Kingsmoot on Old Wyk\">gathering on Old Wyk</a> confirms Euron as king.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Euron offers to give the Seastone Chair to his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Captain_of_the_Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Lord Captain of the Iron Fleet\">Lord Captain of the Iron Fleet</a>, once Euron claims the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> would never seat a stranger in the Seastone Chair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;\"<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Esgred</a>\" to <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">The god</a> took me deep beneath the waves and drowned the worthless thing I was. When he cast me forth again he gave me eyes to see, ears to hear, and a voice to spread his word, that I might be <a href=\"/index.php/Priest_of_the_Drowned_God\" title=\"Priest of the Drowned God\">his prophet</a> and teach his truth to those who have forgotten. I was not made to sit upon the Seastone Chair ... no more than <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Crow's Eye</a>. For I have heard the god, who says, No godless man may sit my Seastone Chair!<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> to his <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_men\" title=\"Drowned men\">drowned men</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Aeron</b>: We shall have no king but from the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot_on_Old_Wyk\" title=\"Kingsmoot on Old Wyk\">kingsmoot</a>. No godless man—<br />\n<b>Euron</b>: —may sit the Seastone Chair, aye. As it happens I have oft sat upon the Seastone Chair of late. It raises no objections.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Asha</b>: Nuncle, hear me. I will place the driftwood crown upon your brow myself ... if you will agree to share the rule.<br />\n<b>Victarion</b>: Share the rule? How could that be? The Seastone Chair seats but one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon</a> has fallen, Balon my brother, who honored the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Way\" title=\"Old Way\">Old Way</a> and paid the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_price\" title=\"Iron price\">iron price</a>. Balon the Brave, Balon the Blessed, Balon Twice-Crowned, who <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_North\" title=\"King of the Isles and the North\">won us back our freedoms</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">our god</a>. Balon is dead ... but an <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_king\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iron king\">iron king</a> shall rise again, to sit upon the Seastone Chair and rule <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">the isles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> to his <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_men\" title=\"Drowned men\">drowned men</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seastone_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History: The Dawn Age.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_24\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 24\">Chapter 24</a>, Theon II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7